  "text": "Security audit of Node.js web stack repositories for CVE-2024-47764 vulnerability in the `cookie` npm package. After systematically searching all target repositories (sg-evals/expressjs-express, sg-evals/nodejs-node, sg-evals/lodash, and sg-evals/prisma-prisma), only one match was found: sg-evals/expressjs-express declares `cookie` version 0.7.1 as a direct runtime dependency in its package.json file. This version is >= 0.7.0, which is the patched version that addresses CVE-2024-47764. The nodejs-node repository contains various package.json files in tools and deps directories, but none declare `cookie` as a direct runtime dependency. The lodash package.json contains no dependencies section at all (only devDependencies). The prisma-prisma repository's packages/client/package.json declares only @prisma/client-runtime-utils as a runtime dependency, with cookie-es (a different package) appearing only in devDependencies."
}

